<subSubSection id="1EF421CCFF8BC12BFF67DF27FE5478C3" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="56517247FF8BC12BFF67DF27FECF7A8A" blockId="17.[151,1437,378,1214]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis id="649AAE55FF8BC12BFF67DF27FEE47AC0" bold="true" box="[151,274,378,404]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="91EE09C4FF8BC12BFEEADF27FE5C7AC0" authorityName="Zahniser" authorityYear="2021" box="[282,426,378,404]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Ackbaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jujuyensis">
<emphasis id="649AAE55FF8BC12BFEEADF27FE5C7AC0" box="[282,426,378,404]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">A. jujuyensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other species in the genus by the male pygofer lacking a posterodorsal spine or tooth and the form of the aedeagus, which has a broad base and narrow shaft curving dorsally and anteriorly.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="56517247FF8BC12BFF37DFB4FD3B7957" blockId="17.[151,1437,378,1214]" box="[199,717,488,515]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis id="649AAE55FF8BC12BFF37DFB4FEFD7957" bold="true" box="[199,267,489,515]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Body.</emphasis>
Male, 
<quantity id="9116DFA2FF8BC12BFEA9DFB5FE447957" box="[345,434,488,515]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" unit="mm" value="4.5">4.5 mm</quantity>
. Metafemur apex 2+2+1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="56517247FF8BC12BFF37DC50FD4C79C2" blockId="17.[151,1437,378,1214]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis id="649AAE55FF8BC12BFF37DC50FEE67973" bold="true" box="[199,272,525,551]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Color.</emphasis>
Anterior margin of head with thin transverse ivory stripe bordered partially above and below with brown; lateral brown stripe distinct from below eye to metacoxa; abdomen with 2 or 3 pairs of poorly defined longitudinal light brown lines. Male tergite VIII with dark pigmentation dorsoapically; pygofer dark brown to black; subgenital plates lightly colored in contrast to dark pygofer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="56517247FF8BC12BFF37DCFCFCB87826" blockId="17.[151,1437,378,1214]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis id="649AAE55FF8BC12BFF37DCFCFEFD79EF" bold="true" box="[199,267,673,699]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Male.</emphasis>
Tergites VII and VIII without macrosetae. Pygofer incised dorsally nearly halfway from apex to base; margin without dorsal blunt tooth, with small caudodorsal hornlike tooth and with several small dentations below, with distinct ventroapical tooth. Subgenital plate with uniseriate lateral row of 6–7 macrosetae; with 1 or 2 other macrosetae near plate apex. Style apophysis straight, digitate, rounded apically; in lateral view with subapical point on ventral side. Aedeagus with base well-differentiated from shaft; shaft narrow, arising caudodorsally from base of aedeagus, curved anterad; gonopore subapical on ventral side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="56517247FF8BC12BFF37DD20FE5478C3" blockId="17.[151,1437,378,1214]" box="[199,418,893,919]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis id="649AAE55FF8BC12BFF37DD20FED378C3" bold="true" box="[199,293,893,919]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
